While former Prime Minister and military General, Umaro Sissoco Embalo, was declared winner of the election by the country's electoral commission, the ruling party has rejected the results and is challenging them in the Supreme Court. 

Despite a pending Supreme Court's decision on a request to annul the election results, Embalo has already sworn himself in as president, while the African Party for the Independence of Guinea and Cape Verde which enjoys a majority in parliament has also installed a rival President who has since resigned. 

For more on this, Channel Africa spoke to Paulin Maurice-Toupane, West Africa Researcher at the Institute for security studies. 

He says the country is sinking deeper into a crisis...

